Dear Friends, 
A Beautiful Morning”(by The Rascals) is out now (links in bio) 🌞 There’s a lot of people I know who are going through very challenging times. So I felt that now is a good time to release this song. Music can help turn a bad day into a good day. Music is medicine. I love the message of this song, it’s about going out into the world and enjoying nature, birds and all the beautiful things that are just outside your door. I hope this song inspires you and I hope you have “a beautiful morning”! Thank you for listening!💕 WIth love and light, Franki x

Sometimes when words aren’t enough, songs make a big difference. Blackbird was written during the 60’s by The Beatles and Paul McCartney said it was symbolic of “racial tension” during the civil rights movement. 
Unfortunately, in 2023 - there is still division - people “hate” others because of what they look like, people attack others online if they say their against - “assault weapons” - people hate others if they wear a mask or don’t wear a mask. If you express who you believe should be president, people will hate you. There seems to be no grey area, just black and white.  The judgement is so thick. No wonder why there are so many people who are depressed. It’s so hard to live in a world with this much judgement. 
I hope that one day, when my child is a woman, that the world has more love and less hate. 
When I sang Blackbird, I sang it in one take. It’s not perfect and that’s how I wanted it. Humans and life aren’t perfect. Nothing’s perfect. 
I want to embrace just being real, in life and in music. There’s so much pressure for everyone to be someone they’re not. 
I believe we’re born to just be our authentic selves and to spread love to others. Love is more powerful than hate. 
Light is more powerful than darkness. 🖤🦅

Artists, to me, are the light workers of our world. I follow a very talented artist on Twitter named @Carney_ART (Patrick Carney). For a long time, I always have been amazed by his paintings of legendary music artists such as : John Lennon, Jim Morrison, Stevie Nicks, etc. One day, which was an absolute shock to me, Patrick posted a painting he created of me on Twitter. I was blown away, I didn’t realize he listened to my music. I just wanted to make this public post to send my sincere gratitude to Patrick for adding me to his collection! It’s such an incredible honor! Thank you Patrick, I’ll always cherish your beautiful artwork! 🙏🎨🖼🖌 #gratitude #spreadlove #artists #painters #lightworkers #appreciationtoartists #artwork #musicportraits #stevienicks #johnlennon #frankilove

Hello Friends! I really love the song “Just The Two Of Us” by Bill Withers and had to do a cover of it! I first recorded this song with guitar but it didn’t feel quite right, so then I tried it with this laid back piano and it felt just right. 💙 My intention with this song was to create a relaxing vibe so you can relax to it. I think we need more relaxation in this world and if I can give that to you, I’ve accomplished mg intentions. I can’t give many of you a physical “hug”, because we’re living all over the world, but I do feel like my songs are “hugs” to you. Many people have been asking me if I’m going to release more originals - -  the answer is “yes”! Over the past 12 months I’ve been working on original songs. More news to come about that in the near future! Until then, “I see the crystal raindrops fall, and the beauty of it all, is when the sun comes shining through” 🌞🌅💖
Have a lovely weekend! 🎶

My little one…

Out of the blue she said, “Mom I want to sing on a big stage”. I thought, really? I have mixed feelings about anyone, especially a child wanting to get into performing/music/show business… I asked her, “Why” - she said… “Just to try it! I really want to try it.” So, the next day, serendipitously I saw an ad for auditions for a talent show ages 5-18 years old at a pretty big venue.  I signed her up. We practiced “True Colors”, just casually in the car. The day the audition came she told me she was nervous. I reminded her, remember, this is just for “fun”… At the audition it was mostly 15-18 year olds. I didn’t know what to expect. It was her first time going up on a big stage with a mic. She got up and every word she sang was beautiful, heartlfelt, I was blown away. I was hysterically crying in the back row. 😭🥺 To see my child get up there, be so brave and just sing from her heart was one of the best days of my life and most proud days for her. 💖🌠 #proudmomma 

#truecolors #mybaby #mygirl #proud

When i was pregnant with my daughter, a lot of people thought i’d stop making music. I stayed home for the first 2 years of her life, nurturing her, savoring every minute. But when she’d fall asleep at 8pm… as exhausted as I was… I’d go on the keyboard with headphones and write songs till 1am. All for the “love” of music. Music is not a “job” for me, it’s a way of life. It’s my connection to the universe and people, that I am 24/7 grateful for. It’s such an honor to be a music artist and am grateful and thankful to all the people who have generously supported me on this journey of music! Without you, I wouldn’t be making a “5th” full length album! For over one year I’ve been developing a new album. Can’t wait to share this one with you! It’s about looking away from your phone, into the sky. Seeing good in the world and in yourself. Indiegogo campaign: coming July 11th!!! 💙

“Fly Like The Wonder You Are” 💜Available everywhere: {link in bio}
Story behind the song 📝this is a song that i re-wrote 4 times. First it was filled with many lyrics, you couldn’t really hear the music. I wrote the song with a standard: verse|chorus|verse|chorus - although i liked the lyrics - when I produce songs and music - i don’t go with what my mind is thinking… i focus completely on how the song makes me feel… with this song… in particular, what I felt was most powerful was the music… it made me feel light and free… like i was flying. I then went through the lyrics and cut out many lyrics. I recorded it again. But the lyrics were still distracting and weighing heavier than the music. At my 4th re-write, I forced myself to remove 80% of the lyrics to just leave a few messages that I thought could lighten up the entire song. The lyrics are simple and free, just like I felt the song should be, hope it makes you feel like flying🕊️

It was my daughters birthday and she asked me if my parents (who are in heaven) would be around her on her birthday. I told her “yes”, they’re always around you, maybe they’ll give us a “sign” today. We got to our hotel, came into the room and went straight to the balcony. We looked up to the sky, it said “LOVE” in the sky, which is her middle name. I knew that was the sign that they were watching over her and were with us. The writing in the sky disappeared within a few mins. It seemed to have vanished. I was glad we got there on time to see it. This song that is playing is “Ocean of Bliss and Inner Peace” it features my daughter, myself and the music of Grammy New Age Composer, Steven Halpern. It’s the last song on my new album “The Sky”. From the feedback I’m getting it seems to be a favorite song on the album. To listen, click the link in the bio. 🩵
.
.

This song is for anyone who had a stressful week or day. Grateful to receive feedback that this song has been helping people.🙏”Ocean of Bliss and Inner Peace”🩵
Steven Halpern & Franki Love 
🎧Song number 9 from The Sky (link in bio) 
✍️ Music Review from music critic, Matthew Baily “Franki saves her longest and most symbolic song for last with the album closer “Ocean of Bliss and Inner Peace”. Not only is this the climactic culmination I was looking forward to from the beginning, but it takes its thematic throughline of the light of love and applies it to the absolute perfect setting: the ocean. Visually, it’s the middle ground between the earth and sky but, as stated by Franki and her daughter (the album’s sole guest vocalist) through brief positive affirmations, it’s the place where you can finally let go of the things holding you back from living a truly fulfilling life, whether it’s fear, anger, regret or grief. Adding Steven Halpern, one of the proclaimed founding fathers of new age music, to this track is a stroke of pure genius as we’re treated to this grand, near-cinematic masterwork of an instrumental from start to finish. Combined with Franki’s singing, vocalizing and whispered messages of hope, the end result is my top favorite song on this album!” 

.
.

For your GRAMMY® consideration…
i don’t create music for awards, in fact, when i meditated and explored the idea of “The Sky” being on the “grammy” ballot for grammy consideration… i was torn… but ultimately ….i realized ….why not? … if the doors open, walk thru them all…. there’s a reason why doors open and why things happen at a certain time… but no matter what, the real “award” is always just being able to express thru music and be a musician and artist… especially during these times in our world, where music is so important to create more peace, love & unity… 🩵☮️🕊️
